          <strong id="Collection">Collection of Personal Data</strong>

          <p>Our Website has many sections that are open to all users, with no account credentials required. All
            information from general visitors to the Website is anonymous and does not contain any Personal Data. The
            web server tracks domain names for security purposes and information regarding the nature and extent of the
            website's usage. This information is used to analyze trends for business purposes such as providing customer
            service, fraud prevention, market research and improving our Website. Please check your Web browser if you
            want to learn what information your browser sends or how to change your settings.</p>

          <p>The VSCPA may collect Personal Data when it is voluntarily submitted by the user to process certain
            requests (such as registration for programs, membership dues, updates and other services). The VSCPA
            collects only the appropriate information needed to process the request voluntarily from the user. Some of
            the information voluntarily collected may include your name, email address, phone number, fax number, postal
            address, membership number, certification information and financial/credit card information. At no point
            does the VSCPA collect any of this information in an involuntary manner. All Personal Data obtained from
            users is treated with great care to protect your privacy and security. The information volunteered is kept
            confidential by the VSCPA and is not shared with unrelated outside parties.</p>

          <p>From time to time, we may use your Personal Data to provide you with updates and other information. We also
            collect the email addresses of people who communicate with us via email. We do not rent, sell or lease email
            addresses to any third party without your consent.</p>

          <p>You may opt out of VSCPA communications at any time.</p>

